>> Under normal circumstances if everything is off you should have
>> infinite resistance if you connect one lead to the positive
>> terminal of the battery and ground the other to the frame or even
>> to the negative terminal but I wouldn't recommend that cause its
>> safer to make your ground connection away from the battery...won't
>> spark and/or ignite hydrogen fumes which may be around battery.
>>  

> unfortunately, if you do that, you will blow the fuse in your meter.
> When checking resistance you must be disconnected from the power
> suply. And if you have a cheap meter, it might not have a fuse,
> you'll just need a new meter.

> - dave -

